WEBVTT

00:06.882 --> 00:08.090
(marching band playing)

00:09.385 --> 00:11.068
Happy Parade Day!

00:11.128 --> 00:14.238
It's the Parade Day Parade!

00:14.298 --> 00:15.589
(horns honking)

00:15.725 --> 00:17.499
Clear the roadway!

00:17.518 --> 00:20.519
Your antics
inconvenience hundreds!

00:21.731 --> 00:23.355
Hooray for parades!

00:23.548 --> 00:25.858
Your antics delight one and all!

00:26.977 --> 00:30.029
Follow me, Little Lord Ralph!

00:31.982 --> 00:34.349
What's hiding
behind the Great Green Wall?

00:34.452 --> 00:35.850
A choo choo? Some buttons?

00:35.953 --> 00:37.852
A dog ten feet tall?

00:37.955 --> 00:40.539
♪ ♪

00:41.584 --> 00:42.624
Hmm-hmm.

00:45.695 --> 00:49.531
(gasps)
My eyes told me a secret!

00:49.550 --> 00:50.716
(school bell rings)

00:50.885 --> 00:53.260
Aw, last day of school.

00:53.387 --> 00:56.221
Lot of fond memories in here.

00:56.390 --> 00:58.540
-Furnace.
-On it.

00:58.559 --> 00:59.874
I know
what's behind the Big Hedge,

00:59.935 --> 01:01.209
because I went behind
the Big Hedge

01:01.270 --> 01:02.710
and I saw what's behind
the Big Hedge

01:02.772 --> 01:04.955
and now I'm gonna tell you. Yay!

01:05.015 --> 01:07.232
The Big Hedge?
As in<i> the</i> Big Hedge?

01:07.425 --> 01:09.717
No one knows
what's behind that thing.

01:09.779 --> 01:12.071
Although,
a seventh grader once told me

01:12.264 --> 01:14.464
it was naked ladies
setting off fireworks.

01:14.483 --> 01:17.801
I heard it's where divorced
parents go to get back together.

01:17.903 --> 01:21.896
No, sir! It's where they hold
the Independent Spirit Awards!

01:21.957 --> 01:24.583
If you call<i> that</i> independent.

01:24.776 --> 01:28.087
No, it's
the best playground ever!

01:28.280 --> 01:31.757
There's Easter eggs and
baby cars that anyone can drive.

01:31.950 --> 01:34.426
And this many clowns
in clown pants!

01:34.619 --> 01:37.805
(chuckles)
Dang, that's hella clowns.

01:39.341 --> 01:40.933
-(raccoon chitters)
-How the crotch

01:41.126 --> 01:42.917
do we get through<i> that</i> thing?

01:42.937 --> 01:44.686
I've seen my dad do this.

01:50.394 --> 01:52.336
(birds chirping)

01:52.396 --> 01:54.279
-Wow!
-OTHERS: Whoa!

01:55.950 --> 01:59.618
See? Easter eggs,
clown pants and baby cars.

01:59.787 --> 02:02.179
I love you, clowns!

02:03.290 --> 02:06.041
There's a golf course
in the middle of Springfield?

02:07.044 --> 02:08.518
NELSON:
What's golf?

02:08.579 --> 02:10.871
I've never seen a golf course
anywhere,

02:10.965 --> 02:12.856
except those commercials
for pills

02:12.916 --> 02:14.949
that give old people
their life back.

02:15.052 --> 02:16.376
-Duckies!
-(ducks quacking)

02:16.470 --> 02:18.879
I'm gonna go steal
their wet bread.

02:18.973 --> 02:22.790
Whoa, I've never seen
Jimbo looking so sharp.

02:22.852 --> 02:24.792
Is he bullying rich guys now?

02:24.854 --> 02:27.128
Fine round today, sir.

02:27.189 --> 02:29.723
You know,
I hope to be a doctor myself.

02:29.817 --> 02:32.484
It's always been my dream
to work around blood.

02:32.653 --> 02:34.319
(laughs)

02:34.512 --> 02:36.947
Well, maybe this will help
with medical school.

02:38.325 --> 02:41.643
Whoa! 20 bucks!

02:41.704 --> 02:43.495
(Jimbo chuckles)

02:43.688 --> 02:45.389
What the hell, Jimbo?
You just suck up to that guy

02:45.490 --> 02:46.648
and he gives you money?

02:46.709 --> 02:48.149
It's not sucking up.

02:48.210 --> 02:50.818
Rich guys love hearing
how great they are,

02:50.880 --> 02:52.654
and they're willing to pay
for it.

02:52.756 --> 02:54.656
Money pay.

02:54.717 --> 02:56.324
Mwah.

02:56.385 --> 02:58.427
Look away, pervs!

03:00.130 --> 03:01.996
We'd like jobs, please.

03:02.057 --> 03:05.350
Well, you seem a little young,
but I do need the help.

03:05.502 --> 03:07.352
I'm out several
of my best caddies

03:07.545 --> 03:09.746
due to an elaborate
virginity-losing wager.

03:09.806 --> 03:11.839
Here are your first assignments.

03:12.860 --> 03:15.936
You know, I've never really
sucked up to anyone before.

03:16.030 --> 03:18.255
Sure, I've lied,
scammed, grifted,

03:18.315 --> 03:20.181
but this feels different.

03:20.242 --> 03:21.366
Special.

03:21.518 --> 03:23.518
Well, I'm a Van Houten.

03:23.579 --> 03:26.112
Watch and learn.

03:26.265 --> 03:29.541
Dang! Looks like I got
the handsomest golfer

03:29.693 --> 03:31.451
in the whole damn club!

03:31.545 --> 03:33.620
-(shudders)
-(groans)

03:33.756 --> 03:36.289
You fine, boy!

03:36.383 --> 03:38.366
Hmm, you're new.

03:38.385 --> 03:41.327
Uh, that's why they
assigned me to you.

03:41.388 --> 03:43.222
The best way to learn the course

03:43.390 --> 03:45.057
is by watching
a master carve it up

03:45.250 --> 03:47.017
like a Thanksgiving turkey.

03:48.253 --> 03:49.427
Hmm.

03:49.621 --> 03:50.787
Hmm. That does sound

03:50.806 --> 03:51.972
like something they would say.

03:52.066 --> 03:54.399
(chuckles)
Let's play some golf.

03:54.592 --> 03:56.068
(exhales):
Whew.

03:56.261 --> 03:57.719
(grunting)

03:57.780 --> 03:59.145
Wait till my friends hear
I caddied

03:59.240 --> 04:01.815
for Kent "The Straight Dope"
Brockman.

04:01.967 --> 04:03.742
We watch you every night.

04:03.935 --> 04:07.079
Really? I thought youngsters got
their news from the Internet.

04:07.230 --> 04:10.898
Pfft. No way. My boys think
broadcast news is the swagness.

04:10.918 --> 04:13.085
And the girls call you
"a snack."

04:13.278 --> 04:15.420
Hope it's okay for me
to use the current lingo.

04:15.613 --> 04:17.422
The snack will allow it.

04:17.615 --> 04:20.241
Stacy and I,
well, it's, uh...

04:20.302 --> 04:21.318
it's complicated.

04:21.420 --> 04:23.077
Isn't it always?

04:23.097 --> 04:25.597
She's a terrific person
and a top-notch meteorologist.

04:25.790 --> 04:28.658
But if I'm dodging her calls
after three months...

04:28.719 --> 04:31.085
I think you've
already made up your mind.

04:31.105 --> 04:33.997
You just don't want to admit it,
'cause you're a kind person.

04:34.057 --> 04:36.191
Mm. Guilty as charged.

04:38.279 --> 04:39.503
You da man!

04:39.563 --> 04:42.506
Muzzle your nonsense, imbecile!

04:42.566 --> 04:44.024
Said da man!

04:44.118 --> 04:45.617
This is "The Straight Dope,"

04:45.786 --> 04:48.011
thanking you
for a wonderful round.

04:48.030 --> 04:49.679
<i> BART:</i>
<i> This is it. The moment of trut.</i>

04:49.740 --> 04:51.272
<i> Did I kiss enough butt?</i>

04:51.292 --> 04:53.517
<i> Only money will tell.</i>

04:53.577 --> 04:55.185
(shudders)

04:55.245 --> 04:57.037
<i> I thought</i>
<i> all money was the same.</i>

04:57.131 --> 04:59.631
<i> But the best money</i>
<i> is peeled off a wad.</i>

04:59.783 --> 05:01.800
♪<i> Cash rules</i>
<i> everything around me</i> ♪

05:01.951 --> 05:03.135
♪<i> C.R.E.A.M., get the money</i> ♪

05:03.286 --> 05:05.211
♪<i> Dollar dollar bill, y'all</i> ♪

05:05.306 --> 05:07.197
