05:12.479 --> 05:13.812
♪<i> C.R.E.A.M., get the money</i> ♪

05:14.005 --> 05:15.722
♪<i> Dollar dollar bill, y'all</i> ♪

05:15.874 --> 05:17.482
♪<i> Cash rules</i>
<i> everything around me</i> ♪

05:17.675 --> 05:19.967
♪<i> C.R.E.A.M., get the money.</i> ♪

05:19.987 --> 05:22.470
There's my number one son.

05:22.531 --> 05:25.807
Come sit next
to your proud papa, workin' man.

05:25.868 --> 05:27.475
We're all proud of you.

05:27.536 --> 05:29.052
I'm sure Bart will learn a lot

05:29.112 --> 05:31.888
carrying a bag of sticks
from place to place.

05:31.990 --> 05:34.816
They're called golf bats, Lis.

05:34.877 --> 05:36.984
Nice starter wad.

05:37.004 --> 05:39.320
You want to see
what I'm rolling with?

05:39.381 --> 05:42.448
Whoa! That rubber band
is just straining!

05:42.551 --> 05:43.567
Can I hold it?

05:43.627 --> 05:44.918
Hey, be careful with that!

05:45.054 --> 05:46.053
-Whoa!
-(Homer moans)

05:47.056 --> 05:49.573
No-static dryer sheets?

05:49.633 --> 05:51.758
You pad your wad?

05:51.852 --> 05:53.334
(gasping)

05:53.354 --> 05:55.261
I'm not the father
you thought you married!

05:55.356 --> 05:57.171
(crying)

05:57.191 --> 05:58.607
-(sprinklers running)
-(golf club strikes ball)

05:59.693 --> 06:00.675
Look, Maggie.

06:00.694 --> 06:02.769
Your brother is doing a job.

06:02.863 --> 06:04.345
Aren't you proud of him?

06:04.406 --> 06:06.013
Aren't you?
(chuckles)

06:06.075 --> 06:07.324
Want to sneak a peek?

06:08.911 --> 06:12.946
...and in the end,
everyone lost money but me.

06:13.040 --> 06:15.356
Wow. I've learned so much today,

06:15.417 --> 06:18.952
about golf, life<i> and</i> oil leases.

06:19.046 --> 06:22.530
I wish I had tribal land
for you to build a pipeline on.

06:22.549 --> 06:25.884
I'd be honored if you'd frack
under my house someday, sir.

06:28.764 --> 06:32.432
Ugh. I've never seen my son...
suck up before.

06:33.802 --> 06:35.452
Easy money. Mwah.

06:35.470 --> 06:38.788
You don't kiss all the golfers'
butts like that, do you?

06:38.807 --> 06:41.900
Oh, Mom. These rich guys expect
a little... (smooching)

06:42.051 --> 06:44.628
in exchange for some... ah.

06:44.646 --> 06:46.053
It's no big deal.

06:46.073 --> 06:48.907
On one hand,
I'm glad you're being polite.

06:49.100 --> 06:50.316
On the other hand...

06:50.452 --> 06:52.411
(shudders loudly)

06:52.604 --> 06:55.580
Wow, I never thought of it
that way, Mom.

06:55.773 --> 06:58.417
No one looks out for me
the way you do.

06:58.610 --> 07:00.401
You are the shining star

07:00.462 --> 07:02.921
that guides this family
through the darkness.

07:03.114 --> 07:05.406
Oh, aren't you sweet.

07:05.467 --> 07:08.242
Why don't we stop by the
skateboard store on the way home

07:08.303 --> 07:09.486
and I'll buy you...
(gasps)

07:09.588 --> 07:10.595
(grumbles)

07:10.788 --> 07:11.746
Suck-up.

07:11.807 --> 07:13.223
(cackling)

07:17.995 --> 07:20.013
So, there we are
on the 18th green.

07:20.165 --> 07:21.831
The course has been a bear
all morning.

07:21.892 --> 07:24.017
I tell Judge Snyder
to shut that all out

07:24.169 --> 07:25.426
and just be in the moment.

07:25.487 --> 07:27.612
-He nods, plants his feet.
-(gasps) Mm-hmm?

07:27.764 --> 07:29.839
-And, in one smooth motion...
-Mm?

07:29.900 --> 07:32.701
-...tips me 50 bucks!
-(gasps)

07:33.620 --> 07:35.862
Wow. Just... wow.

07:36.014 --> 07:38.698
Why do I suddenly want
to bring Bart's car around?

07:38.792 --> 07:40.500
(Bart humming)

07:42.004 --> 07:44.296
Here you go.
Buy yourself a bigger tip jar.

07:44.489 --> 07:45.705
(bell dings)

07:45.799 --> 07:47.524
(plays note on harmonica)

07:47.584 --> 07:49.526
♪<i> Tip's in the jar,</i>
<i> grateful we are</i> ♪

07:49.544 --> 07:51.544
♪<i> Praised be your name,</i>
<i> you've raised the game</i> ♪

07:51.638 --> 07:53.454
♪<i> Some give us zip,</i>
<i> it's such a rip</i> ♪

07:53.474 --> 07:55.381
♪<i> Shame them with song,</i>
<i> they're in the wrong</i> ♪

07:55.476 --> 07:56.808
♪<i> All of the grown-ups</i>
<i> in here just...</i> ♪

07:57.001 --> 07:58.218
Doesn't it bother you

07:58.312 --> 07:59.886
that Bart made that money...

07:59.980 --> 08:02.630
(quietly): sucking up
to those golfers?

08:02.691 --> 08:04.966
Marge, sucking up
is the American way.

08:04.985 --> 08:06.634
In this country,
everybody got together

08:06.695 --> 08:08.895
and decided that all the money
should belong

08:09.047 --> 08:11.881
to a few dozen families
<i> and</i> their favorite suck-ups.

08:11.942 --> 08:15.309
Don't you remember
when we all decided that?

08:15.370 --> 08:17.478
-(groans)
-And of all the things

08:17.539 --> 08:19.164
that Bart might do for money,

08:19.357 --> 08:21.407
this is by far the most legal.

08:21.560 --> 08:23.335
Other people are paying our son.

08:23.486 --> 08:24.853
And in cash!

08:24.880 --> 08:27.822
It's both aboveboard
and under the table.

08:27.883 --> 08:29.916
That's the dream!

08:30.052 --> 08:32.252
Homie, I know it's not logical,

08:32.387 --> 08:34.420
but when I saw Bart
at that golf course,

08:34.556 --> 08:37.590
my mothering spirit
just wanted to hurl.

08:37.743 --> 08:39.592
Back me up on this one.

08:39.686 --> 08:42.078
Tell our son he has to quit.

08:42.138 --> 08:44.264
Quit being a caddy? No way!

08:44.358 --> 08:46.266
How much did Mom give you
to tell me that?

08:46.360 --> 08:48.601
Uh... n-nothing.

08:48.695 --> 08:50.028
Well, I can do better than that.

08:50.221 --> 08:52.272
Will 20 bucks make this go away?

08:52.366 --> 08:54.941
Well, I guess I can tell her
I did my best.

08:55.035 --> 08:58.278
Tell her you did your...
<i> very</i> best.

08:58.372 --> 08:59.687
Mm-hmm.

08:59.790 --> 09:02.098
Now that you got your own pool,

09:02.117 --> 09:04.117
what are you gonna buy next?

09:04.211 --> 09:05.526
I'm thinking
of getting one of those booths

09:05.629 --> 09:07.120
that blows money around.

09:07.272 --> 09:09.122
It pays for itself
the first time you get in it.

09:09.216 --> 09:10.607
Bart, no!

09:10.667 --> 09:12.551
That wad is your future.

09:12.719 --> 09:15.554
What you need is
a good investment vehicle.

09:15.722 --> 09:16.888
Hmm.

09:17.933 --> 09:19.449
(all exclaiming)

09:19.509 --> 09:23.210
"Patented Ultra-Freedom
BadAss Technology

09:23.230 --> 09:26.106
stops the engine if the driver
puts on a helmet."

09:26.215 --> 09:27.381
-Yes!
-Yeah!

09:27.401 --> 09:29.568
After you buy it,
can we have rides?

09:29.761 --> 09:32.237
Guys, guys,
if I shared my death-mobile,

09:32.430 --> 09:35.073
then you wouldn't be motivated
to earn wads of your own.

09:35.266 --> 09:36.908
I'm doing this for you.

09:37.101 --> 09:40.153
Yeah, well,
you're acting like a butt wad.

09:40.289 --> 09:41.988
(chuckles):
Oh, Nelson.

09:42.082 --> 09:44.641
Saying what you really think
will get you nowhere.

09:44.659 --> 09:46.251
-Lousy rich kids.
-(grumbling, muttering)

09:46.420 --> 09:47.752
-MARTIN: If I had a quad,
I'd share my quad.
-Lame.

09:47.945 --> 09:49.879
(huffing angrily)

09:51.091 --> 09:52.257
Mm!

09:52.426 --> 09:55.743
(grumbling loudly)

09:55.762 --> 09:57.987
Okay, okay, I'll tell you
what's bothering me.

09:58.089 --> 09:59.656
It's Bart's caddy job.

09:59.758 --> 10:00.932
It's gross, right?

10:01.125 --> 10:02.434
You can tell me it's gross.

10:02.627 --> 10:03.918
You think it's gross?

10:03.937 --> 10:06.754
Well, private golf clubs
are pretty evil.

10:06.815 --> 10:08.348
Right. They are.

10:08.442 --> 10:09.774
How so?

10:11.445 --> 10:13.169
Wow, look at all these.

10:13.229 --> 10:15.171
Waste of water resources,

10:15.231 --> 10:16.356
pesticide use,

10:16.450 --> 10:18.450
history of sexism and racism...

10:18.619 --> 10:20.510
And Bart's a suck-up!

10:20.528 --> 10:22.178
Not to mention
that private clubs

10:22.238 --> 10:25.181
get huge breaks
on their property taxes,

10:25.241 --> 10:26.866
which is completely unfair.

10:26.960 --> 10:29.185
Why shouldn't rich people pay
their share?

10:29.245 --> 10:31.612
Lisa, we've got
to shut down that club.

10:31.748 --> 10:33.965
We're going to city hall!

10:34.158 --> 10:35.884
♪ ♪

10:36.803 --> 10:38.219
(golf ball clacks)

10:39.831 --> 10:41.723
(both grumbling)

10:46.188 --> 10:48.521
-(snarling)
-Oh!

10:51.676 --> 10:53.985
Club President Bildorf.

10:54.154 --> 10:55.803
Plays every single day

10:55.864 --> 10:58.305
and never tips less
than 100 bucks.

10:58.367 --> 11:01.642
(whistles) Looks like I picked
the right summer job.

11:01.662 --> 11:04.329
Mark my words--
his bag will be on my shoulder

11:04.522 --> 11:06.313
before this year's Father-Son

11:06.375 --> 11:09.726
Bingo-Bango-Bongo
Best-Ball Scramble.

11:09.744 --> 11:10.985
You know,
since school's not in session,

11:11.046 --> 11:13.079
I can finally tell you...

11:13.231 --> 11:14.673
you're awesome.

11:15.700 --> 11:17.417
-Mm...
-Hmm? Hmm?

11:17.552 --> 11:19.219
I'll take Simpson.

11:22.373 --> 11:23.256
(chuckles)

11:23.392 --> 11:25.166
Eh, I just won't play.

11:25.185 --> 11:25.850
Mm.

11:26.002 --> 11:27.427
♪ ♪

11:27.521 --> 11:30.021
Okay, Mom. You got
to get your voice out there.

11:30.173 --> 11:31.856
Take the cause
directly to the people

11:32.049 --> 11:34.192
with an online petition.

11:35.854 --> 11:37.320
I got this!

11:38.189 --> 11:39.923
There.

11:40.024 --> 11:42.183
Now all I need is
a catchy title.

11:42.244 --> 11:43.259
(gasps)
I got it.

11:43.319 --> 11:44.928
"Stop Coddling

11:44.988 --> 11:47.447
the Springfield Junipers
Wealthy."

11:47.541 --> 11:49.115
Whoops, too long. Hmm.

11:49.209 --> 11:51.601
How about "Stop Coddling

11:51.661 --> 11:53.119
the S.J.W.s."

11:53.213 --> 11:54.862
And post.

11:54.881 --> 11:57.440
I wonder if that headline
will get any attention.

11:57.500 --> 12:00.719
An online petition attacking
our local private golf club

12:00.887 --> 12:03.613
has garnered
over one million signatures.

12:03.673 --> 12:05.724
-(both gasp)
-One million?

12:05.917 --> 12:07.392
(gasps)
Mom,

12:07.585 --> 12:10.377
you used the term "S.J.W."

12:10.397 --> 12:11.712
Yes, I know.

12:11.732 --> 12:13.456
The "Springfield Junipers
Wealthy."

12:13.516 --> 12:17.736
No! "S.J.W." stands for
"social justice warriors."

12:17.929 --> 12:20.221
That's what right-wing trolls
call anyone who cares

12:20.282 --> 12:22.056
about positive social change.

12:22.117 --> 12:24.150
Look at the other
online petitions

12:24.286 --> 12:26.411
your "supporters" have backed.

12:26.604 --> 12:28.913
MARGE:
Oh, boy.

12:29.106 --> 12:32.233
Um, a signature's a signature?

12:32.294 --> 12:33.585
Thanks to the cranky clicks
collected

12:33.778 --> 12:35.661
by local complainer
Marge Simpson,

12:35.814 --> 12:37.238
Springfield's golf club
will have to pay

12:37.299 --> 12:39.148
a huge property tax increase,

12:39.167 --> 12:41.317
threatening
the club's very existence.

12:41.419 --> 12:43.669
In one reporter's
unbiased opinion,

12:43.822 --> 12:47.657
closing this par-72 landmark
would be a travesty.

12:47.675 --> 12:48.933
One and all would mourn the loss

12:49.085 --> 12:51.102
of this exclusive
private green space

12:51.254 --> 12:53.438
and Ramon's famous Bloody Marys.

12:53.631 --> 12:56.065
He uses a golf tee
as an olive skewer.

12:57.060 --> 12:58.668
I think it's Ramon.

12:58.728 --> 13:00.670
I finally found something
I'm good at,

13:00.730 --> 13:02.688
and you want to ruin it!

13:02.824 --> 13:05.341
You don't know what it's like to
bring something into this world,

13:05.401 --> 13:08.678
watch it grow and worry about it
day and night.

13:08.738 --> 13:10.363
I love you, Wad.

13:10.457 --> 13:12.624
We're going shopping
for rubber bands.

13:12.817 --> 13:15.034
You deserve it!

13:15.128 --> 13:18.187
Simpson,
report to the first tee.

13:18.248 --> 13:20.206
You're going to the show.

13:20.300 --> 13:21.466
Yes!

13:22.886 --> 13:26.137
<i> Digitaria sanguinalis.</i>

13:26.330 --> 13:29.048
Tell Tetsuo he's fired.

13:29.142 --> 13:31.226
I think it's Tetsuo.

13:32.628 --> 13:34.628
Mr. Club President?

13:34.689 --> 13:36.463
I'm sorry,
for a second there,

13:36.483 --> 13:38.817
I mistook you
for a young Pierce Brosnan.

13:39.010 --> 13:39.967
Very young.

13:40.070 --> 13:41.227
Ha!

13:41.321 --> 13:43.655
Spare me, kid.
I've heard it all.

13:43.824 --> 13:48.142
Simpson, your mother's campaign
is going to bankrupt this club.

13:48.161 --> 13:50.311
I need you to convince her
to call it off.

13:50.330 --> 13:51.979
Oh, I am trying.

13:52.040 --> 13:54.499
My mom never backs down,
no matter how wrong she is.

13:54.692 --> 13:56.150
(gasps)

13:56.211 --> 13:58.670
That's why
she's still married to my dad!

13:58.863 --> 14:02.156
(stammers) Why are charities
and churches

14:02.217 --> 14:05.735
the only ones
that don't have to pay taxes?

14:05.753 --> 14:07.828
(chuckles):
It's preposterous.

14:07.889 --> 14:11.165
Yeah, man, this place
is better than any church.

14:11.226 --> 14:13.242
Everyone wants
to come here on Sunday,

14:13.261 --> 14:15.186
people are always shouting out
the Lord's name

14:15.379 --> 14:16.913
and, instead of wafers and wine,

14:16.973 --> 14:20.433
you get club sandwiches
and scotch in a plastic cup!

14:20.527 --> 14:21.934
Bart Simpson,

14:22.087 --> 14:24.253
you've just given me
the greatest idea

14:24.314 --> 14:27.773
since little whales embroidered
on khakis.

14:27.868 --> 14:29.659
(whales singing)

14:30.787 --> 14:33.279
As of today, the sport of golf

14:33.373 --> 14:35.431
is officially declared
a religion.

14:35.491 --> 14:37.191
The Springfield Junipers
Golf Club

14:37.252 --> 14:39.285
is now a house of worship.

14:39.379 --> 14:42.772
Like all religions, golf
will be completely tax-exempt,

14:42.832 --> 14:44.716
adhering
to the core American credo

14:44.885 --> 14:46.885
that churches rake it in
but pay nothing.

14:47.053 --> 14:49.387
May Golf have mercy on us all.

14:50.432 --> 14:52.056
Mm.

14:52.225 --> 14:53.516
(groans)

14:56.512 --> 14:57.787
-(crowd oohing)
-MAN: Get in the hole!

14:57.847 --> 14:59.622
(excited murmuring)

14:59.682 --> 15:01.691
(cheering)

15:08.407 --> 15:10.408
Thank you for coming,
Your Holinesses.

15:10.601 --> 15:11.984
Once you see how these golfers

15:12.078 --> 15:14.820
are cheapening
the whole idea of religion,

15:14.915 --> 15:17.306
you'll put an end to this sham.

15:17.325 --> 15:20.810
You want me to cast judgment
on a faith other than my own?

15:20.828 --> 15:22.754
Well, twist my arm.

15:22.947 --> 15:24.330
(laughing)

15:24.424 --> 15:26.740
♪<i> I'm alright, Lordy, Lordy</i> ♪

15:26.801 --> 15:29.594
♪<i> Don't nobody worry 'bout me,</i>
<i> don't worry</i> ♪

15:29.745 --> 15:31.578
♪<i> You got to gimme a fight</i> ♪

15:31.640 --> 15:33.673
♪<i> Why don't you</i>
<i> just let me be?</i> ♪

15:33.767 --> 15:34.674
♪<i> Hallelujah!</i> ♪

15:34.826 --> 15:35.992
Mm?

15:36.052 --> 15:38.494
Congregants,
scripture, prayer--

15:38.554 --> 15:41.105
looks like a house of worship
to me.

15:41.257 --> 15:42.832
(Marge grumbles)

15:42.892 --> 15:44.667
These aren't commandments.

15:44.727 --> 15:46.335
They're jokes I don't get.

15:46.396 --> 15:49.072
Well, there's plenty of saints.

15:50.266 --> 15:51.674
(Italian accent):
Blessed Shark,

15:51.734 --> 15:54.360
deliver my son's golf ball
safely

15:54.512 --> 15:57.472
onto the green
of Pebble Beach's notorious

15:57.474 --> 16:00.750
and evil 17th hole.

16:02.870 --> 16:05.705
Look at this! It's like
the high holidays every day.

16:05.857 --> 16:07.023
I should be so lucky.

16:07.041 --> 16:08.541
Marge, I'm sorry,

16:08.635 --> 16:11.285
but I think this religion
checks all the boxes.

16:11.388 --> 16:13.721
We're calling it.
It's a faith.

16:17.519 --> 16:20.478
I just can't take
seeing him like this.

16:20.671 --> 16:22.647
Honey, over the years
I've learned

16:22.798 --> 16:25.149
that you just want me
to listen to your problems

16:25.342 --> 16:26.818
and not always try
to solve them.

16:27.011 --> 16:28.736
So... good luck.

16:33.184 --> 16:35.051
It's Sunday.
Shouldn't you be in church?

16:35.069 --> 16:36.402
I mean,<i> your</i> church.

16:36.554 --> 16:39.238
(sighs) I've said a lot to you
about this job,

16:39.390 --> 16:40.981
except what's deepest
in my heart.

16:41.042 --> 16:44.151
Honey, the thing I've
always admired most about you

16:44.212 --> 16:47.488
is that you've never needed
anyone else's approval.

16:47.507 --> 16:49.398
And I'm worried
you're gonna lose that.

16:49.459 --> 16:51.325
I'm not gonna suck up forever.

16:51.386 --> 16:52.918
Just until I'm rich.

16:53.054 --> 16:55.847
Then other people
will suck up to<i> me.</i>

16:55.998 --> 16:58.424
Promise me these golf people
won't take away

16:58.518 --> 17:00.167
my special little guy,

17:00.228 --> 17:03.246
because they seem to get
everything else they want.

17:03.264 --> 17:04.439
Mwah.

17:11.388 --> 17:13.105
Ready to play, sir?

17:13.199 --> 17:14.681
I see you've got
a new diamond earring.

17:14.743 --> 17:16.200
Very age-appropriate.

17:16.352 --> 17:19.111
Bart, you'll never caddy
for me again.

17:19.247 --> 17:21.447
Now that your mother's
no longer a threat,

17:21.541 --> 17:23.933
I can go back
to Chadlington here.

17:23.951 --> 17:27.361
Him?! But<i> my</i> religion idea
saved the club!

17:27.497 --> 17:28.938
I should be your caddy.

17:28.998 --> 17:30.030
I earned it!

17:30.091 --> 17:31.365
Earned?

17:31.468 --> 17:34.385
Earning things is so...

17:34.554 --> 17:35.386
tennis.

17:35.597 --> 17:38.056
Golf is about privilege.

17:38.224 --> 17:40.800
Fine. But someday
I'm gonna be a member here,

17:40.952 --> 17:43.210
and I'm gonna be cool
to the caddies.

17:43.271 --> 17:45.121
Uh, you, a member?

17:45.181 --> 17:47.047
(laughing):
Oh, look,

17:47.108 --> 17:48.900
you made Chadlington laugh.

17:49.093 --> 17:50.902
(high-pitched chuckling)

17:51.095 --> 17:54.388
Look, there's no path from where
you are to where I am.

17:54.491 --> 17:57.366
Once a suck-up,
always a suck-up.

17:58.453 --> 18:00.136
(grunts)

18:00.238 --> 18:01.621
-♪
-(panting)

18:04.125 --> 18:05.208
Mm?

18:06.735 --> 18:08.086
Well, I earned<i> this.</i>

18:08.279 --> 18:11.714
Sorry, buddy,
but it's time to say goodbye.

18:12.783 --> 18:13.740
(golf club strikes ball)

18:13.802 --> 18:14.984
-Ah!
-LOVEJOY: Fore!

18:15.086 --> 18:16.260
<i> You</i> joined?

18:16.453 --> 18:17.837
They gave us a group deal.

18:17.989 --> 18:19.655
<i> And</i> they lifted
their restrictions.

18:19.757 --> 18:20.765
What's not to like?

18:20.916 --> 18:22.491
Everything's not to like!

18:22.552 --> 18:24.084
These people are horrible.

18:24.145 --> 18:26.679
Their stupid shoes
clack-clack-clack everywhere.

18:26.773 --> 18:30.015
The snack shop buffalo wings
are microwaved and...

18:30.151 --> 18:32.944
-(engine revving)
-What the...?

18:33.095 --> 18:35.863
♪ ♪

18:40.903 --> 18:42.203
